00:00:16.960 --> 00:00:23.619
Hey guys it's Jess, and first up, at last
weekend's PAX East in Boston, 2k and Firaxis

00:00:23.619 --> 00:00:25.820
announced Civilization: Beyond Earth.

00:00:25.820 --> 00:00:30.210
It's the latest title in the Sid Meier's Civilization
series, and is a continuation of the same

00:00:30.210 --> 00:00:33.390
gameplay you loved from the franchise, but
this time it's in space!

00:00:33.390 --> 00:00:39.000
The developers had to think outside the box
and come up with new planets, races, systems...it's

00:00:39.000 --> 00:00:42.560
a pretty ambitious project, and we grabbed
an interview with the producers at PAX East,

00:00:42.560 --> 00:00:46.050
we'll link that to you in the description
below.

00:00:46.050 --> 00:00:50.449
Marty O'Donnell, the composer known for his
iconic work with the Halo franchise, has been

00:00:50.449 --> 00:00:51.910
let go from Bungie.

00:00:51.910 --> 00:00:56.190
No official reason has been given, with O'Donnell
simply tweeting that Bungie's board of directors

00:00:56.190 --> 00:00:58.440
terminated him without cause on April 11th.

00:00:58.440 --> 00:01:02.980
To many, he was seen as an asset in the Halo
community, and had been most recently working

00:01:02.980 --> 00:01:07.200
on the Destiny soundtrack, making this termination
all the more surprising.

