00:01:36.080 --> 00:01:41.130
CCP's next MMO World of Darkness has been
canceled, resulting in a layoff of 56 employees

00:01:41.130 --> 00:01:42.770
at their Atlanta office.

00:01:42.770 --> 00:01:46.780
The game had been a long time in the making,
first revealed 8 years ago, and CEO Hilmar

00:01:46.780 --> 00:01:50.970
Veigar Petursson said in a prepared statement
that canceling the title was one of the hardest

00:01:50.970 --> 00:01:53.009
decisions he's ever had to make.

00:01:53.009 --> 00:01:58.280
Following the cancellation, it was revealed
that CCP had recorded a loss of $21 million

00:01:58.280 --> 00:02:02.899
during the 2013 financial year, and that the
primary reason for the company's drop in profit

00:02:02.899 --> 00:02:08.229
was an increase in R&amp;D costs related to EVE
Valkyrie, Dust 514, and World of Darkness.

00:02:08.229 --> 00:02:13.640
Crystal Dynamics has posted some new job listings
to fill roles working on Tomb Raider 2 - and

00:02:13.640 --> 00:02:17.570
while we've known for a while that this sequel
to the franchise reboot was underway, we've

00:02:17.570 --> 00:02:20.570
now been given a slight glimpse into some
of the gameplay elements.

00:02:20.570 --> 00:02:26.190
We now know that it will be cinematic heavy,
and like its predecessor will feature stealth

00:02:26.190 --> 00:02:28.800
and RPG-lite elements, as well as an economy.

00:02:28.800 --> 00:02:32.840
Go ahead and click the link in the video description
if you want to view the Crystal Dynamics job

00:02:32.840 --> 00:02:33.930
listings for yourself.

